Title: Example Pre-submission Study (teaching sample, not a real manuscript)

Abstract

This text stands in for a manuscript so the auditor has a document to read. It describes
a control versus treatment comparison shown in Figure 1A (microscopy) and a protein-level
comparison shown in Figure 2A (immunoblot).

Figures and sources

Figure 1A is exported from the raw acquisition in raw_images/acquisition_001.png. Figure 2A
is cropped from the full membrane image in raw_images/full_membrane_002.png. The structured
manifest in figure_assembly/assembly_manifest.csv records these figure-to-raw relationships.
Quantitative summaries are in source_data/Figure_1_source.csv and source_data/Figure_2_source.csv.

Methods (abbreviated)

Group assignment used a block random number table. Outcome scoring was blinded. Exclusion
criteria were defined before analysis. Sample sizes, means, standard deviations, standard
errors, and p-values are reported in the supplied source-data tables. A sample map and
methods notes are included under protocols/, and analysis notes are under statistics_code/.

Not included in this example

Supplementary files and ethics/IACUC approval records are intentionally omitted so the
audit demonstrates how missing materials are reported as completeness gaps.
